post_text:
Important Information on Eden CISD Graduation

On Monday, April 27th, Texas Gov. Greg Abbott stated he will allow his shelter-in-place order to expire on Thursday, April 30th. Based on this information Eden CISD will be moving forward with its regularly scheduled in-person graduation ceremony that is planned for Friday, May 22nd.

TEA is working with public health specialists and a superintendent task force to identify the circumstances under which an in-person ceremony may occur. Guidelines for in-person graduation ceremonies will be made available as soon as possible.

Thank you all for your patience as we work toward making graduation the special event that it should be for the Eden High School Class of 2020.

TEA is working with public health specialists and a superintendent task force to identify the circumstances under which an in-person ceremony may occur. Guidelines for in-person graduation ceremonies will be made available as soon as possible.

Thank you all for your patience as we work toward making graduation the special event that it should be for the Eden High School Class of 2020.

As most of you know, we will remain closed at least until May 4th.

Moving forward, please make sure that your children are turning in their assignments and that they/you are staying in contact with their teachers. These are the two most important things to do to make sure that your child continues to be academically successful.

If you have questions or concerns about classwork reach out to teachers for help.

If you are having problems w/ technology you can contact Mrs. Dillard at kelli.dillard@edencisd.net

If you need anything from me, I can be contacted at matt.odom@edencisd.net

Most importantly, stay safe and healthy!

Eden CISD
March 25 at 11:41 AM ¬∑

Our district will be participating in the Summer Meals-to-You program, and it's sign-up time! We offered this program for the first time last summer, and had a tremendous amount of success. We are also currently in the process of applying to participate in an Emergency Meals-to-You program that has been started due to COVID-19 school related closures. Please keep watching our Facebook page for more information about that. In the meantime, if your child receives free/reduced meals at school, and you'd like to sign up for the summer program, please visit https://mealstoyou.org/meals-to-you-texas/ to sign up. The deadline is March 30th. If you have questions or need to request student IDs, please contact Cierra Briggs at cierra.briggs@edencisd.net

Eden CISD
March 14 at 8:13 PM ¬∑

Like most districts in our region, we are going to extend our spring break for the week March 16 - 20. Information on the COVID-19 virus changes constantly. Our district will be proactive in getting educational services planned in the event of a long-term closure in the future.

Students will not be in school next week. Our teachers will have work days on Wednesday and Thursday (March 18-19).

Our teachers will be working on how to best serve our students in case of a closure. We also need to plan on how to get meals to our students in the event that school closes long term.

We understand that our decisions have far-reaching consequences on the community at large. We appreciate your patience as we move through these uncertain times.

As spring break ends, students and staff may be returning home following travel. To have a safe re-entry to the school, Eden CISD is requesting that our students and staff follow CDC guidelines for self-reporting. We need to know if you:

1. Have tested positive for COVID-19
2. Have been in close contact with someone who has tested positive for the COVID-19 virus
3. Have been to an area with a high concentration of COVID-19 virus

To notify the district, please send an email to edencisd_enrollment@edencisd.net. All information reported will be kept confidential.
